# CorpFlow Candidate & Reference Library — auto-merge

**Canonical library name:** `CorpFlow Candidate & Reference Library`

Anton has **standing permission** to auto-merge without separate manual approval when a PR **clearly belongs to this library** and **all** conditions below hold.

## Library scope (docs capture only)

- Product candidates, tool references, article references
- Benchmark products, future roadmap references, destination-shape notes
- Marketing automation candidates, AI video/article generation candidates
- Future chat/concierge references
- Operator-supplied rationale for why a tool is worth tracking

**Index:** `docs/product/README.md`

## Allowed paths (unless repo convention says otherwise)

- `docs/product/**`, `docs/strategy/**`, `docs/research/**`, `docs/tools/**`
- `artifacts/chat_history.md`
- `.cursor/rules/library-capture-auto-merge.mdc` (when updating this policy)
- Lightweight index in `docs/CORPFLOW_SHARED_TODO.md` **only if** a relevant library section already exists
- `docs/decisions/JOURNAL.md` **only if** repo convention requires a JE row

## Allowed capture statuses

- `REFERENCE-ONLY`, `DESTINATION-SHAPE`, `CANDIDATE-CAPTURED`, `SERIOUS-CANDIDATE / EVALUATE-FIRST`, `NO IMPLEMENTATION AUTHORIZED`

**Do not use** `AUTHORIZED`, `SELECTED`, `IMPLEMENTING`, or `COMPLETE` unless Anton **separately and explicitly** authorizes implementation.

## Auto-merge requirements (narrow)

- Docs-only PR; `git diff --name-only` ⊆ allowed paths above
- No app/runtime code, `.env*`, new env var names, secrets, tokens, credentials, private URLs, chat IDs, passwords, API keys, or Infisical paths
- No n8n workflow changes; no L3/server commands
- No Docker/containers, GitHub Actions, scripts, cron, systemd, database/schema changes, API routes, middleware, package files, Vercel config, or public endpoints
- PR body or captured doc must state **`NO IMPLEMENTATION AUTHORIZED`**
- Preserve standing holds: no restic (unless separately authorized), no new self-hosted tools, no Chatwoot/Open WebUI/Dify/Coolify/Langfuse/AgentSpan/OpenJarvis/generic chatbot frameworks, no n8n migration, no public port exposure, no additional containers

## Pre-merge verification

1. `git diff --stat` is docs-only
2. `git diff --name-only` ⊆ allowed paths
3. No secret-like strings, tokens, private URLs, chat IDs, API keys, passwords, or Infisical paths
4. PR explicitly says **`NO IMPLEMENTATION AUTHORIZED`**
5. CI/checks green if applicable

## Do not auto-merge if

- PR is not clearly a **CorpFlow Candidate & Reference Library** update
- Any app/runtime, env, infrastructure, monitoring, backup, n8n, deployment, auth, database, or production-behavior change
- Implementation wording or tool authorization ambiguity
- CI fails or merge conflicts exist

If blocked, **stop and ask Anton**.

## Post-merge response format

Report: **Status** / **What I checked** / **What changed** / **Merge SHA** / **Confirmation that this was a CorpFlow Candidate & Reference Library update** / **Confirmation that no implementation was authorized**
